{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Eye tracking is a technology that records eye movements and gaze locations over time (Carter and Luke, 2020), and has seen increased usage in research over recent years.",
    "The scanpath is an important concept in eye tracking, and it refers to the trace of a user's eye movements across space over a period of time (Holmqvist et al., 2011).",
    "Scanpaths are closely associated with two eye tracking terms: fixations and saccades.",
    "Fixations describe the state when the eyes remain relatively still for a time period lasting between a few tens of milliseconds up to a few seconds, while saccades are the rapid eye movements from one fixation to another (Holmqvist et al., 2011).",
    "The combination of both fixations and saccades produces a scanpath."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Eye tracking is a technology that records eye movements and gaze locations over time (Carter and Luke, 2020), and has seen increased usage in research over recent years.",
    "The scanpath is an important concept in eye tracking, and it refers to the trace of a user's eye movements across space over a period of time (Holmqvist et al., 2011).",
    "Fixations describe the state when the eyes remain relatively still for a time period lasting between a few tens of milliseconds up to a few seconds, while saccades are the rapid eye movements from one fixation to another (Holmqvist et al., 2011)."
  ]
}